      "text": "React Events",
      "level": "h1"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Just like HTML DOM events, React can perform actions based on user events.",
      "html": "<p class=\"intro\">Just like HTML DOM events, React can perform actions based on user events.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "React has the same events as HTML: click, change, mouseover etc.",
      "html": "<p class=\"intro\">React has the same events as HTML: click, change, mouseover etc.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "metadata": {
        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "Adding Events",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "React events are written in camelCase syntax:",
      "html": "<p>React events are written in camelCase syntax:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "onClick instead of onclick .",
      "html": "<p><code>onClick</code>\ninstead of <code>onclick</code>.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "React event handlers are written inside curly braces:",
      "html": "<p>React event handlers are written inside curly \nbraces:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "onClick={shoot} instead of onclick=\"shoot()\" .",
      "html": "<p><code>onClick={shoot}</code>\u00a0 instead of\n<code>onclick=\"shoot()\"</code>. </p>"
    },
